comments: Work on your senior thesis and upload components to the website.
Required and a good thing to do a yearlong project.

You have to do it, but it's incredibly rewarding. Meet with your advisor and librarian often and don't be shy in waiting awhile before picking a topic. It's much better to have a good topic late than it is to have a bad topic early.
I would recommend it if you want to graduate as a history major.

I thought the two-semester senior essay for the History major was going to be awesome. It turned out to be a waste of time. My advisor said he didn't care what I did. We met twice. Over Thanksgiving I read a few books and summarized them for my 10-page requirement. What a silly process, emblematic of a lack of caring by the History department
Absolutely enroll in this course if you would like to graduate! Highly recommended.
Very self-directed work, not much structure throughout the term

This is the first semester of the senior essay for History majors. It's when we finalize your topic, research, develop a focus, and begin constructing an argument. There are due dates spaced throughout the semester for different writing assignments related to the senior essay.
hey, if you're a history major... you're in this. dassit.
It is a very important part of completing your Senior Essay because it forces you to think and develop your topic or potential topics throughout the entire year.
